HEADWORD: Exceptious
<hw>Ex*cep"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Disposed or apt
to take exceptions, or to object; captious.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At least effectually silence the doubtful and
<qex>exceptious</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ex*cep"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms> <rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exceptive</ent>⟦br⟧
